      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. B. October 10</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>World Mental Health Day&nbsp;</strong>was celebrated for the <strong>first time on October 10, 1992</strong>, at the initiative of <strong>Deputy Secretary General Richard Hunter</strong>.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>World Mental Health Day&nbsp;</strong>is celebrated every year on <strong>October 10th</strong>. This <strong>day</strong> is dedicated to <strong>raising awareness</strong> of <strong>mental health</strong> issues around the world and mobilizing efforts in support of mental health.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: IAPSM textbook, 1<sup>st</sup> ed, pg. 814</strong></span></p>",
