      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34762,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. D. During his lifetime, person can be dependent on only one drug.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option D:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Drug dependence</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">, as a <strong>complex medical condition</strong>, does <strong>not limit</strong> an <strong>individual</strong> to <strong>dependency</strong> on a <strong>single drug</strong> throughout their lifetime. In reality, <strong>individuals</strong> can <strong>develop dependencies</strong> on <strong>multiple substances</strong> at <strong>different times</strong> or simultaneously. The <strong>nature</strong> of <strong>substance use disorders</strong> is such that they can involve a <strong>range of substances</strong>, and <strong>dependence</strong> can <strong>shift or evolve</strong> based on various factors including <strong>availability</strong>, <strong>personal circumstances</strong>, and underlying mental health conditions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option</span></strong>&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A. Interaction between a living organism and a drug:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">This is a <strong>core component</strong> of <strong>drug dependence</strong>, describing the physiological and psychological interactions that underpin addiction.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option</span></strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>B. Characterized by behavioral and other responses:</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Dependence&nbsp;</strong>is indeed <strong>marked by behavioral changes</strong>, often including an <strong>intense focus</strong> on <strong>obtaining</strong> and using the substance, alongside other psychological and physiological responses.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option</span></strong>&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">C. Compulsion to take the drug on a periodic or continuous basis:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A hallmark of <strong>drug dependence</strong> is a <strong>strong</strong> or <strong>uncontrollable urge</strong> to <strong>use the substance</strong>, whether sporadically or continuously, often to avoid withdrawal symptoms or to achieve a desired psychological state.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Drug dependence&nbsp;</span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">is described as &ldquo;<strong>a state, psychic</strong> and <strong>sometimes also physical</strong>, resulting from the <strong>interaction</strong> between a <strong>living organism</strong> and a <strong>drug</strong>, characterized by <strong>behavioral</strong> and other <strong>responses</strong> that always include a <strong>compulsion to take the drug</strong> on a <strong>continuous</strong> or <strong>periodic basis</strong> to experience its <strong>psychic effects</strong>, and sometimes to avoid the discomfort of its absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A person may be dependent upon more than one drug.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg. 928</span></strong></span></span></p>",
